Boil the Maggi cake in a vessel and drain the water. Heat a pan and saut√© the chopped onions in it till they are golden brown and tomatoes are soft. Add the masalas (+ the Maggi masala tastemaker) and cook for a minute.

Add the boiled noodles to the pan and stir well. Voila, Indian Tadka Maggi is ready. Pro tip: Garnish it with coriander leaves and fried onions to outdo the pulao. 